            "content": "# Plan: Pane Archive — Keep Closed Pane History\n\n## Context\n\nThe current implementation already has:\n- Readable `session--window--pane.txt` filenames\n- `history-limit 0` (unlimited scrollback)\n- 30s capture cycle via `session-logger.sh`\n- `_tsh_function.fish` parsing filenames to jump to sessions\n\nThe remaining gap: when a pane closes, the next cycle rotates its `.txt` to `.old` and then **deletes it**, losing the last known state forever. The user wants closed-pane snapshots preserved for later searching — but split into per-pane files (not a single blob), and kept ergonomic.\n\n---\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Update `session-logger.sh` — archive closed panes instead of deleting\n\n**File:** `home-manager/programs/tmux/session-logger.sh`\n\nChange the rotation logic:\n\n- After recapturing all live panes, check each `.old` file\n- If a matching `.txt` exists → pane still alive → delete the `.old` (unchanged behaviour)\n- If **no** matching `.txt` exists → pane closed → move to `archive/` with a timestamp suffix\n\n```sh\n#!/usr/bin/env sh\nmkdir -p ~/.local/share/tmux/panes\nmkdir -p ~/.local/share/tmux/archive\nLOG=~/.local/share/tmux/session-history.log\nPANE_DIR=~/.local/share/tmux/panes\nARCHIVE_DIR=~/.local/share/tmux/archive\n\nwhile true; do\n  sleep 30\n\n  # Append window metadata\n  tmux list-windows -a \\\n    -F \"$(date +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S)  #{session_name}:#{window_index}  #{window_name}  #{pane_current_path}\" \\\n    >> \"$LOG\" 2>/dev/null\n\n  # Rotate existing live snapshots to .old\n  for f in \"$PANE_DIR\"/*.txt; do\n    [ -f \"$f\" ] && mv \"$f\" \"${f%.txt}.old\"\n  done\n\n  # Recapture all currently live panes\n  tmux list-panes -a -F \"#{session_name} #{window_index} #{pane_index} #{pane_id}\" \\\n    2>/dev/null | while IFS= read -r line; do\n      sess=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      widx=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f2)\n      pidx=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f3)\n      pane_id=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f4)\n      tmux capture-pane -pt \"$pane_id\" -S - 2>/dev/null \\\n        > \"$PANE_DIR/$sess--$widx--$pidx.txt\"\n    done\n\n  # For each .old: if a live .txt exists → pane survived → delete .old\n  #                if no live .txt  → pane closed  → archive with timestamp\n  ts=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\n  for old in \"$PANE_DIR\"/*.old; do\n    [ -f \"$old\" ] || continue\n    base=$(basename \"${old%.old}\")\n    if [ -f \"$PANE_DIR/$base.txt\" ]; then\n      rm -f \"$old\"\n    else\n      mv \"$old\" \"$ARCHIVE_DIR/${base}--${ts}.txt\"\n    fi\n  done\ndone\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Update `_tsh_function.fish` — search archive too\n\n**File:** `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tsh_function.fish`\n\n- Add `archive_dir` variable pointing at `~/.local/share/tmux/archive`\n- Pass both `$pane_dir` and `$archive_dir` to `rg -l` so search covers live + closed panes\n- Parse filenames from archive: `work--0--0--20260226-103000.txt` → sess=`work`, widx=`0`\n  - Strip the trailing `--<timestamp>` before splitting on `--`\n  - Since archived panes no longer exist, skip the `tmux has-session` jump and instead just print the file path / preview content\n\nThe archive filename format `sess--widx--pidx--YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.txt` lets us extract `parts[1]` and `parts[2]` the same way as live files. For dead sessions, we print a message but still show the content.\n\n```fish\nfunction _tsh_function --description \"Search tmux session history log or pane contents\"\n  set -l log ~/.local/share/tmux/session-history.log\n  set -l pane_dir ~/.local/share/tmux/panes\n  set -l archive_dir ~/.local/share/tmux/archive\n\n  if test (count $argv) -gt 0\n    if not test -d \"$pane_dir\"\n      echo \"No pane content store found at $pane_dir\"\n      return\n    end\n\n    set -l query (string join ' ' $argv)\n    set -l selected (rg -l -- \"$query\" \"$pane_dir\" \"$archive_dir\" 2>/dev/null \\\n      | fzf --prompt=\"pane-search> \" \\\n            --height=40% \\\n            --preview=\"rg -n -- '$query' {} 2>/dev/null | head -80\" \\\n            --preview-window=right:60%)\n\n    if test -z \"$selected\"\n      return\n    end\n\n    # work--0--0.txt or work--0--0--20260226-103000.txt → sess=work, widx=0\n    set -l fname (string replace -r '.*/' '' \"$selected\" | string replace -r '--\\d{8}-\\d{6}\\.txt$' '' | string replace '.txt' '')\n    set -l parts (string split -- '--' $fname)\n    set -l sess $parts[1]\n    set -l widx $parts[2]\n\n    if not tmux has-session -t \"$sess\" 2>/dev/null\n      echo \"Session '$sess' no longer exists (archived pane — content shown above in preview)\"\n      return\n    end\n\n    if test -n \"$TMUX\"\n      tmux switch-client -t \"$sess\"\n      tmux select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\" 2>/dev/null\n    else\n      tmux attach-session -t \"$sess\" \\; select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\"\n    end\n    return\n  end\n\n  # No argument: fzf over the history log\n  if not test -f \"$log\"\n    echo \"No session history found at $log\"\n    return\n  end\n\n  set -l selected (cat \"$log\" | fzf \\\n    --prompt=\"session-history> \" \\\n    --height=40% \\\n    --tac \\\n    --no-sort \\\n    --preview='echo {}')\n\n  if test -z \"$selected\"\n    return\n  end\n\n  set -l target (string split '  ' $selected)[2]\n  set -l parts (string split ':' $target)\n  set -l sess $parts[1]\n  set -l widx $parts[2]\n\n  if not tmux has-session -t \"$sess\" 2>/dev/null\n    echo \"Session '$sess' no longer exists\"\n    return\n  end\n\n  if test -n \"$TMUX\"\n    tmux switch-client -t \"$sess\"\n    tmux select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\" 2>/dev/null\n  else\n    tmux attach-session -t \"$sess\" \\; select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\"\n  end\nend\n```\n\n---\n\n## Final directory layout\n\n```\n~/.local/share/tmux/\n├── session-history.log              # window metadata log (grows unbounded)\n├── panes/\n│   ├── work--0--0.txt               # live pane snapshots (overwritten each cycle)\n│   └── dotfiles--0--0.txt\n└── archive/\n    ├── work--0--0--20260226-103000.txt   # closed pane, last snapshot before close\n    └── work--1--0--20260226-091500.txt\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `home-manager/programs/tmux/session-logger.sh` | Replace `rm -f *.old` with archive-or-delete logic |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tsh_function.fish` | Search `archive/` too; handle archive filename format; graceful message for dead sessions |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Open a pane, wait 30s → `panes/work--0--0.txt` exists\n2. Close that pane, wait 30s → `panes/work--0--0.txt` gone, `archive/work--0--0--<ts>.txt` exists\n3. `tsh <text that was in the closed pane>` → fzf shows the archive file, preview shows matching lines\n4. Selecting an archived pane prints \"Session no longer exists\" rather than erroring\n5. `tsh <text in live pane>` → still navigates to the live session/window as before\n",
