sion_name} #{window_index} #{pane_index} #{pane_id}\" \\\n    2>/dev/null | while IFS= read -r line; do\n      sess=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f1)\n      widx=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f2)\n      pidx=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f3)\n      pane_id=$(printf '%s' \"$line\" | cut -d' ' -f4)\n      tmux capture-pane -pt \"$pane_id\" -S - 2>/dev/null \\\n        > \"$PANE_DIR/$sess--$widx--$pidx.txt\"\n    done\n\n  rm -f \"$PANE_DIR\"/*.old 2>/dev/null\ndone\n```\n\n**Update:** `home-manager/programs/tmux/default.nix` — replace the inline `text = ''...''` block with a file source:\n\n```nix\nhome.file.\".config/tmux/session-logger.sh\" = {\n  executable = true;\n  source = ./session-logger.sh;\n};\n```\n\nKey changes vs current:\n- **Standalone file** — no Nix string escaping, easier to edit/test directly\n- **Readable names** — `work--0--0.txt` instead of `3.txt`\n- **Stale cleanup** — rotate-to-`.old`, recreate live, delete `.old`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Update `_tsh_function` to parse filename\n\n**File:** `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tsh_function.fish`\n\nReplace the metadata-header parsing with filename parsing:\n\n```fish\n# work--0--0.txt → sess=work, widx=0\nset -l fname (string replace -r '.*/' '' \"$selected\" | string replace '.txt' '')\nset -l parts (string split -- '--' $fname)\nset -l sess $parts[1]\nset -l widx $parts[2]\n```\n\nRemove the `head -n 1` / `string match -rg 'session=...'` lines.\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify / Create\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `home-manager/programs/tmux/tmux.conf` | Add `set -g history-limit 50000` |\n| `home-manager/programs/tmux/session-logger.sh` | **create** — standalone script |\n| `home-manager/programs/tmux/default.nix` | Replace inline `text=` with `source = ./session-logger.sh` |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tsh_function.fish` | Parse session/window from filename, drop header parsing |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n1. After server restart, `~/.local/share/