efault.nix` | **create** — `xdg.configFile.\"tmuxinator\".source = ./tmuxinator` |\n| `config/tmuxinator/tmuxinator/primary.yml` | **create** |\n| `config/tmuxinator/tmuxinator/mobile.yml` | **create** |\n| `config/tmuxinator/tmuxinator/desktop.yml` | **create** |\n| `config/tmuxinator/tmuxinator/work.yml` | **create** |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tpo_function.fish` | Use tmuxinator on first create |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tmo_function.fish` | Use tmuxinator on first create |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tdo_function.fish` | Use tmuxinator on first create |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_two_function.fish` | Use tmuxinator on first create |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tss_function.fish` | Use tmuxinator for default sessions |\n\n## Verification\n1. After `home-manager switch`, run `tpo` with no existing `primary` session → tmuxinator creates it with 3 windows (editor, shell, server)\n2. Run `tpo` again → attaches/switches normally without re-applying layout\n3. Run `tss`, select `mobile` (non-existent) → tmuxinator creates it with 2 windows\n4. Run `tss`, select an existing session → switch/attach as before\n5. Run `tss`, type a new ad-hoc name → plain `tmux new-session` (no YAML needed)\n",
