it '  ' $selected)[1]   # \"session:index\"\n  set -l parts (string split ':' $target)\n  set -l sess $parts[1]\n  set -l widx $parts[2]\n\n  if test -n \"$TMUX\"\n    tmux switch-client -t \"$sess\"\n    tmux select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\"\n  else\n    tmux attach-session -t \"$sess\" \\; select-window -t \"$sess:$widx\"\n  end\nend\n```\n\nRegister in **`home-manager/programs/fish/default.nix`**:\n- Add `\"_twf_function\"` to the `xdg.configFile` function list (alphabetical between `_tss_function` and `_two_function`)\n- Add `twf = \"_twf_function\";` to `shellAbbrs`\n\n---\n\n### 3. `tmux.conf` — last-session toggle + window picker bind\n\nAdd two lines to **`home-manager/programs/tmux/tmux.conf`** in the bindings section:\n\n```\n# Last session (quick flip)\nbind Tab switch-client -l\n\n# Cross-session window picker\nbind W run-shell \"tmux new-window 'fish -c _twf_function'\"\n```\n\n`Tab` is currently unbound. `W` is currently unbound (lowercase `w` is default select-window by index, not bound here).\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n\n| File | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tss_function.fish` | Add preview + ctrl-x kill to fzf call |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_twf_function.fish` | **create** — cross-session window picker |\n| `home-manager/programs/fish/default.nix` | Add `_twf_function` to list + `twf` abbr |\n| `home-manager/programs/tmux/tmux.conf` | Add `bind Tab switch-client -l` and `bind W` |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `tss` → hover over a session → right panel shows numbered windows\n2. `tss` → hover over a session → press `ctrl-x` → session is killed, picker closes\n3. `twf` (or `prefix+W` inside tmux) → lists all windows from all sessions → select one → lands in the right session+window\n4. Inside tmux, press `prefix+Tab` → switches to the previously active session instantly\n",
