            "content": "# Plan: Tmux Sessionizer with Default Sessions\n\n## Context\nThe dotfiles already have 4 named tmux sessions managed individually via fish functions:\n- `tpo` → `primary`, `tmo` → `mobile`, `tdo` → `desktop`, `two` → `work`\n\nThe goal is a **sessionizer** — an fzf-powered picker that lists default sessions, creates them if missing, and switches to them. This replaces manually typing `tpo`/`tmo` etc. and ensures default sessions always exist.\n\nExisting relevant pieces:\n- `home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_t{po,mo,do,wo}_function.fish` — individual session attach fns\n- `home-manager/programs/fish/default.nix` — shellAbbrs + xdg.configFile function list\n- `home-manager/programs/tmux/tmux.conf` — tmux keybinds, `tmux-sessionx` bound to `o`\n- `tmux-resurrect` + `tmux-continuum` already configured for session persistence\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. New fish function: `_tmux_sessionizer_function.fish`\n\n`home-manager/programs/fish/functions/_tmux_sessionizer_function.fish`\n\n```fish\nfunction _tmux_sessionizer_function --description \"Fuzzy-pick or create a tmux session\"\n  set default_sessions primary mobile desktop work\n\n  # Build candidate list: default sessions first, then existing sessions not in default list\n  set existing (tmux list-sessions -F '#S' 2>/dev/null)\n  set candidates $default_sessions\n  for s in $existing\n    if not contains $s $default_sessions\n      set -a candidates $s\n    end\n  end\n\n  set selected (printf '%s\\n' $candidates | fzf --prompt=\"session> \" --height=40%)\n  test -z \"$selected\" && return\n\n  if tmux has-session -t \"$selected\" 2>/dev/null\n    if test -n \"$TMUX\"\n      tmux switch-client -t \"$selected\"\n    else\n      tmux attach-session -t \"$selected\"\n    end\n  else\n    tmux new-session -d -s \"$selected\"\n    if test -n \"$TMUX\"\n      tmux switch-client -t \"$selected\"\n    else\n      tmux attach-session -t \"$selected\"\n    end\n  end\nend\n```\n\n### 2. Register 